The food was sooo good. Wasn't expecting it to be that good at a bar. And great music too. Whatever the gravy/sauce they put on the pork + veggies is freakin DELICIOUS. And their fried rice with over easy eggs on top is hella good too. That dish is enough to feed like 6-8 people, easy. And try their watermelon and li hing soju cocktails. SOOO good. Staff is always super helpful too and always checking up or going extra mile. It's my favorite spot for good eats, good drinks, and good vibes.

the atmosphere is pure aloha and a place of acceptance. This is a place where all the locals go to hangout and enjoy the island nightlife and somewhat like a "Backyard Luau Kanikapila". Famous local artists and Halau's perform at this little humble lounge. There's entertainment, Karaoke, and dart boards. The drinks are unique and a must try........The Pickled Mango Drink, and the Pokemon are the two that I have encountered and recommended! I saved the best for last..... The food!!!  I loved the fried rice. It was very tasty and the portion was for at least 4 people. The steak was unbelievable!!!!  Mo Betta Den Ruth's Chris..... I tell you!!! Flavourful, juicy and tender!  My only problem with this steak was, not having enough room in belly to fit more!!!  Everyone..... I mean Everyone is welcomed and made to feel safe to be who you are at the Imua Lounge!!!
